data.title: Z Databases
data.text:
The following databases are newly acquired or being evaluated for a future subscription.

AM Explorer This link opens in a new window

New

AM Explorer provides access to 130+ digital primary source collections, with archives spanning the fifteenth to twenty-first centuries, across the humanities and social sciences. Access ends 12/31/24.

Gale Business: Entrepreneurship This link opens in a new window

New

Contains real business plans, how-to guides, articles, and more.

Gale Business: Insights This link opens in a new window

New

An extensive collection of business intelligence, combining Gale reference content with respected business sources and full-text periodicals to help researchers understand todayâ€™s global business environment. Users can access more than 430,000 detailed company profiles with company financial data, in-depth country overviews, and comprehensive i ndustry profiles to stay current with the ever-evolving business landscape.

Gale Health and Wellness This link opens in a new window

New

Health-focused magazines, reference, video, and more.

Gale Legal Forms This link opens in a new window

New

Create accurate, reliable legal documents with no hassle.

Gale OneFile: Leadership and Management This link opens in a new window

New

Articles on leadership and management, and more.

Gale OneFile: News This link opens in a new window

New

Provides access to more than 2,300 major U.S. regional, national, and local newspapers (including the New York Times), as well as leading titles from around the world. It also includes thousands of images, radio and TV broadcasts and transcripts.

Gale Presents: Peterson's Test and Career Prep This link opens in a new window

New

Search thousands of college and graduate schools, identify scholarships, take practice tests, create resumes, and explore careers.

Geological Surveys Database This link opens in a new window

New

Discover publications from the state geographical surveys and factsheets from the United States Geological Survey (USGS). Some links to full text.

Pangaea This link opens in a new window

New

Open access data repository that archives, publishes and distributes georeferenced data from earth system research.
